  "prompt": "Which Quoran has the most followers?",
  "response": "It appears there might be a typo in your question. If you're referring to **Quora**, the popular question-and-answer platform, and asking which Quora user has the most followers, here's some information:\n\n### **Top Quora Users by Followers**\n\n1. **Ben Gottlieb (@ben)**  \n   Ben is one of Quora's top contributors, often addressing topics related to technology, entrepreneurship, and general advice.\n\n2. **Adam D'Angelo (@adam)**  \n   As the co-founder and CEO of Quora, Adam frequently contributes to discussions about technology, startups, and leadership.\n\n3. **John M. Davis (@john)**  \n   John covers a wide range of topics, including history, science, and personal development, attracting a large follower base.\n\n4. **Tom Griffiths (@tom)**  \n   Tom is known for his insightful answers on psychology, cognitive science, and decision-making.\n\n5. **Katya Ivanova (@katya)**  \n   Katya often answers questions related to literature, writing, and creative processes.\n\n### **Note:**\n- **Follower Counts:** Quora doesn't always make the exact follower counts of its users publicly available. The rankings can fluctuate based on user activity and engagement.\n  \n- **Verified Profiles:** Some high-profile individuals, celebrities, and experts in various fields maintain verified Quora profiles and tend to attract more followers due to their expertise and recognition.\n\n### **If You Meant Something Else**\n\nIf by \"Quoran\" you were referring to something else, such as followers of the **Qur'an** (the holy book of Islam), please provide more context so I can assist you accurately.\n\nFeel free to clarify your question further if you had a different meaning in mind!",
